.TH KRAKEN 1 "2026-06-13" "0.1.0" "Kraken Manual"
.SH NAME
kraken \- Autonomous coding agent and security tool
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B kraken
[OPTIONS] [COMMAND]
.SH DESCRIPTION
Kraken is an autonomous coding agent with offensive security capabilities:
vulnerability scanning, OSINT, secret detection, and LLM-powered automation.
.PP
It connects to multiple LLM providers (Anthropic, OpenAI, DeepSeek, Ollama)
to function as an AI-powered coding and security assistant.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-\-help
Print help information
.TP
.B \-\-version
Print version information
.TP
.BI \-\-model " MODEL"
Select the LLM model to use
.TP
.BI \-\-provider " PROVIDER"
Select the LLM provider (anthropic, openai, deepseek, ollama, dashscope)
.TP
.B \-\-output-format json
Emit machine-readable JSON output
.TP
.B \-\-resume " SESSION"
Resume an existing session
.TP
.B \-\-compact
Use compact mode (shorter responses)
.TP
.BI \-\-reasoning-effort " LEVEL"
Set reasoning effort (low, medium, high)
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
.B kraken [PROMPT]
Start REPL or run a one-shot prompt
.TP
.B kraken doctor
Run health check and diagnostics
.TP
.B kraken status
Show session and configuration status
.TP
.B kraken init
Initialize project configuration
.TP
.B kraken vulnscan
Scan for vulnerabilities
.TP
.B kraken login
Authenticate with LLM provider
.SH SLASH COMMANDS
Once in the REPL, available commands include:
.PP
/bash, /read, /write, /edit, /glob, /grep,
/web_search, /web_fetch, /agent, /task,
/vulnscan, /osint, /doctor, /status,
/session, /history, /diff, /export,
/memory, /config, /help, /model
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B ANTHROPIC_API_KEY
API key for Anthropic Claude
.TP
.B DEEPSEEK_API_KEY
API key for DeepSeek
.TP
.B OPENAI_API_KEY
API key for OpenAI-compatible providers
.TP
.B ANTHROPIC_BASE_URL
Custom API endpoint URL
.SH FILES
.TP
.I .kraken.json
Project-specific configuration
.TP
.I ~/.config/kraken/config.json
User-global configuration
.SH BUGS
Report issues at https://github.com/rooselvelt6/kraken/issues
.SH SECURITY
Report vulnerabilities according to SECURITY.md
